# Stressed-Test
This script develops a predictive modeling pipeline for ODR by first loading historical ODR and macroeconomic variable (MEV) data from Excel, then identifying statistically significant MEV variables for each sector using a Generalized Linear Model (GLM). It systematically evaluates all possible combinations of these significant variables, incorporating lagged ODR and a time trend, to determine the best-performing model based on error metrics such as RMSE and R²
Once the optimal model is selected for each sector, the script generates in-sample predictions and performs out-of-sample forecasting using projected MEV data in an iterative manner, where previous predictions feed into subsequent periods. Finally, it consolidates the results—including model evaluation metrics, predicted values, and forecast outputs—into a structured Excel file for further analysis and reporting
